==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*arƀma-'', from Indo-European ''*orbh-''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[erm]], Old Saxon [[arm]] (Dutch [[arm]]), Old High German [[arm]] (German [[arm]]), Old Norse [[armr]] (Swedish, Danish [[arm]]), Gothic [[𐌰𐍂𐌼𐍃]].

